        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 9 at 4:40PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 440 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles south of Ryegate, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph, along with occasional lightning
and brief moderate rainfall.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Mainly rural areas of South Central Golden Valley and North
Central Stillwater Counties, south of Highway 12.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
